T1	Intervention 303 714	This was a multicenter, randomized, double-blind, placebo controlled study. Thirty-eight mechanically ventilated patients with documented nosocomial pneumonia were included. Patients treated with intravenous betalactam and tobramycin were randomly allocated to receive aerosolized tobramycin (6 mg/kg/day, n = 21) or placebo (n = 17). The aerosol was administered via a pneumatic nebulizer once a day for 5 days
